The narrative hints at a corrupted alternate reality where familiar heroes took darker paths, drawing Doctor Doom into the heart of the multiversal crisis and threatening total collapse across worlds. snippet.title: DC DAYS X KITHADIKIRAN | Trailer Launch Turned into Surprise üò≤ | DC Days  Meet at UB City
snippet.description:
Yesterday was totally an unexpected and memorable day for us ‚ù§Ô∏è

Me and my friend, YouTuber Typical Kannadiga, were planning to attend the Trailer Launch Event of the Kannada movie ‚ÄúNayana Manohara‚Äù, which was held at the iconic UB City, Bangalore.
This beautiful film is produced by Anush Siddappa, and the entire event was very well organised.

But the real twist of the day was something we never expected üòçüî•

üëâ Suddenly, we met DC Days Kannada YouTuber ‚Äì Deepak Chauhan, along with his wife Vidhya K H.
It was our first ever meet, and honestly, it felt so warm, friendly, and joyful. We had a wonderful conversation, shared laughs, and spoke a lot about YouTube, content creation, and life in general ü§ù‚ú®
Such humble and down-to-earth people ‚ù§Ô∏è

Along with this, my close friends
üîπ Nishanth from Digi Peps Marketing Agency
üîπ Ajith Kumar
üîπ Monish from Powerrad CUSTOMS
üîπ Thanvi from Digi Peps

were also present, and together we had non-stop fun, discussions, and great vibes üòÑüî•
It truly felt like a perfect creators‚Äô meetup.

A special mention to the ‚ÄúNayana Manohara‚Äù film team üôè
They welcomed us very warmly and even gave us gifts as part of the welcome ceremony, which made the experience even more special ‚ù§Ô∏èüéÅ
The hospitality and respect they showed towards creators was really commendable.

Overall, this trailer launch event turned into an unexpected, fun-filled, and memorable day that we will always cherish.
Don‚Äôt miss watching this vlog till the end ‚Äì surprises guaranteed üòçüé•

If you liked the video,
üëâ Like üëç
üëâ Share üîÅ
üëâ Subscribe ‚ù§Ô∏è

‚Äì Kithadi Kiran

‚∏ª

snippet.title: Dastan-E-Ma Gujri | Sandhu Surjit | Balraj | G Guri | GGM Entertainment | Devotional 2025
snippet.description:
‚ÄúDastan-E-Mata Gujri‚Äù is not just a song ‚Äî it is a sacred narration of Sikh history.
From the birth of Mata Gujri Ji to the journey of her life filled with faith, patience, and sacrifice,
this song beautifully portrays every chapter, leading up to the eternal martyrdom of the Chhote Sahibzade.
It is a heartfelt tribute to the unshakable courage of Mata Gujri Ji,
her spiritual strength, and her unwavering devotion to righteousness.
Each verse carries the pain, pride, and glory of a mother whose sacrifice shaped history.
This soulful composition is meant to touch every heart
that respects the legacy of Sikh martyrs and the timeless values they stood for.



Singer: Sandhu Surjit & Balraj
Music by: G Guri
Lyrics: Sandhu Surjit
Visual Vdo: Harsh Chopra 
MixMaster: Beat King 
Producer: G Guri & Amritpal Singh
Label: GGM Entertainment

snippet.description:
#OmSakthiOm #AmmanSongs #MaruvathoorAmman #AmmanSongs #LREswari #Veeramanidasan #Mahanadhi Shobana #BhaktiMaalai

The album "‡Æì‡ÆÆ‡Øç ‡Æö‡Æï‡Øç‡Æ§‡Æø ‡Æì‡ÆÆ‡Øç - Om Sakthi Om is dedicated to Goddess Amman. This album has 3 songs sung by L.R Eswari, Veeramanidasan .
Lyrics By : Mugilan 
Music By : Kanmani Raja, D.V.Ramani
Produced by Unique Recording
‡ÆÆ‡Øá‡Æ≤‡Øç‡ÆÆ‡Æ∞‡ØÅ‡Æµ‡Æ§‡Øç‡Æ§‡ØÇ‡Æ∞‡Øç ‡ÆÜ‡Æ§‡Æø‡Æ™‡Æ∞‡Ææ‡Æö‡Æï‡Øç‡Æ§‡Æø ‡Æö‡Æø‡Æ±‚Äå‡Æ™‡Øç‡Æ™‡ØÅ ‡Æ™‡Ææ‡Æü‚Äå‡Æ≤‡Øç‡Æï‚Äå‡Æ≥‡Øç

Amman is the South Indian Goddess of Rain. She is the main South Indian mother/goddess in the southern India. Mari is closely associated with the Hindu goddess Parvati and Durga. 
Her festivals are held during the late summer/early autumn season of Aadi throughout Tamil Nadu and Deccan region, the largest being Aadi Thiruvizha. Devotees offer Pongal that is cooked using earthen pots which are made during the festive season. Rituals such as fire walking and mouth or nose piercing are also practised. Mari in Tamil means rain. Thus she is referred to as Mariyayee or Aathaa. Aathaa means mother or grandmother. She symbolizes sacrifice, motherhood, abundant wealth and good health. 

May Goddess Amman Bless You All!

The album "‡Æì‡ÆÆ‡Øç ‡Æö‡Æï‡Øç‡Æ§‡Æø ‡Æì‡ÆÆ‡Øç - Om Sakthi Om is dedicated to Goddess Amman. This album has 3 songs sung by L.R Eswari, Veeramanidasan .

Produced by Unique Recording
‡ÆÆ‡Øá‡Æ≤‡Øç‡ÆÆ‡Æ∞‡ØÅ‡Æµ‡Æ§‡Øç‡Æ§‡ØÇ‡Æ∞‡Øç ‡ÆÜ‡Æ§‡Æø‡Æ™‡Æ∞‡Ææ‡Æö‡Æï‡Øç‡Æ§‡Æø ‡Æö‡Æø‡Æ±‚Äå‡Æ™‡Øç‡Æ™‡ØÅ ‡Æ™‡Ææ‡Æü‚Äå‡Æ≤‡Øç‡Æï‚Äå‡Æ≥‡Øç

Amman is the South Indian Goddess of Rain. She is the main South Indian mother/goddess in the southern India. Mari is closely associated with the Hindu goddess Parvati and Durga. 
Her festivals are held during the late summer/early autumn season of Aadi throughout Tamil Nadu and Deccan region, the largest being Aadi Thiruvizha. Devotees offer Pongal that is cooked using earthen pots which are made during the festive season. Rituals such as fire walking and mouth or nose piercing are also practised. Mari in Tamil means rain. Thus she is referred to as Mariyayee or Aathaa. Aathaa means mother or grandmother. She symbolizes sacrifice, motherhood, abundant wealth and good health. 

May Goddess Amman Bless You All!

The album "‡Æì‡ÆÆ‡Øç ‡Æö‡Æï‡Øç‡Æ§‡Æø ‡Æì‡ÆÆ‡Øç - Om Sakthi Om is dedicated to Goddess Amman. This album has 3 songs sung by L.R Eswari, Veeramanidasan .
Lyrics By : Mugilan 
Music By : Kanmani Raja, D.V.Ramani
Produced by Unique Recording
‡ÆÆ‡Øá‡Æ≤‡Øç‡ÆÆ‡Æ∞‡ØÅ‡Æµ‡Æ§‡Øç‡Æ§‡ØÇ‡Æ∞‡Øç ‡ÆÜ‡Æ§‡Æø‡Æ™‡Æ∞‡Ææ‡Æö‡Æï‡Øç‡Æ§‡Æø ‡Æö‡Æø‡Æ±‚Äå‡Æ™‡Øç‡Æ™‡ØÅ ‡Æ™‡Ææ‡Æü‚Äå‡Æ≤‡Øç‡Æï‚Äå‡Æ≥‡Øç

Amman is the South Indian Goddess of Rain. She is the main South Indian mother/goddess in the southern India. Mari is closely associated with the Hindu goddess Parvati and Durga. 
Her festivals are held during the late summer/early autumn season of Aadi throughout Tamil Nadu and Deccan region, the largest being Aadi Thiruvizha. Devotees offer Pongal that is cooked using earthen pots which are made during the festive season. Rituals such as fire walking and mouth or nose piercing are also practised. Mari in Tamil means rain. Thus she is referred to as Mariyayee or Aathaa. Aathaa means mother or grandmother. She symbolizes sacrifice, motherhood, abundant wealth and good health. 

May Goddess Amman Bless You All!

laago 302 ya Macoca
